The paper discusses the use of native and translation-based solutions for analysis problems in Graph Transformation Systems (GTSs), which are typically studied in the sub-fields of software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), logic (cs.LO), formal languages (cs.FL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also cites literature on the application of theorem provers, model checkers, and SAT/SMT solvers in GTSs, which are commonly used in these sub-fields. Therefore, cs.SE is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, and cs.AI.
